{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Alias","symbolKind":"typealias","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19SpawnChildSetupFunca","role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSpawnChildSetupFunc","text":"GSpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX platforms, the function is called in the child after GLib","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has performed all the setup it plans to perform, but before calling","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"exec()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Actions taken in this function will only affect the child,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not the parent."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows, the function is called in the parent. Its usefulness on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Windows is thus questionable. In many cases executing the child setup","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function in the parent can have ill effects, and you should be very","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"careful when porting software to Windows that uses child setup","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, even on POSIX, you are extremely limited in what you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"safely do from a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc"},{"type":"text","text":", because any mutexes that were"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"held by other threads in the parent process at the time of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will still be locked in the child process, and they will never be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unlocked (since the threads that held them don’t exist in the child).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"POSIX allows only async-signal-safe functions (see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signal(7)"},{"type":"text","text":") to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"called in the child between "},{"code":"fork()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"text":", which drastically limits","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the usefulness of child setup functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In particular, it is not safe to call any function which may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call ","type":"text"},{"code":"malloc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which includes POSIX functions such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setenv()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If you need to set up the child environment differently from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the parent, you should use "},{"code":"g_get_environ()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_setenv()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_environ_unsetenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and then pass the complete environment"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"list to the "},{"code":"g_spawn...","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_sync()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which can, in very","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SpawnChildSetupFunc":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to "},{"code":"g_spawn_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_spawn_sync()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}}}